<subSubSection pageId="21" pageNumber="88" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,348,438,464]" box="[227,348,438,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,348,438,464]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="88" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,348,438,464]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,1437,485,582]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">
Species of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ryckholt" authorityYear="1852" box="[356,506,485,511]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="21" pageNumber="88" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[356,506,485,511]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Vestinautilus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with moderately depressed, rounded-trapezoidal whorl profile (ww/wh ~1.60– 1.80), venter weakly flattened, with three longitudinal grooves on each side, ventrolateral shoulder subangular. Whorls weakly embracing. Ornament with two or three weak but sharp ridges on the flank.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection box="[227,1302,621,694]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,362,621,647]" box="[227,362,621,647]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,362,621,647]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="88" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,362,621,647]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Etymology</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,1302,667,694]" box="[227,1302,667,694]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">
From the Latin ‘ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Korn &amp; Bockwinkel" authorityYear="2022" box="[420,503,667,693]" class="Cephalopoda" family="Trigonoceratidae" genus="Vestinautilus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Nautilida" pageId="21" pageNumber="88" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="papilio">
<emphasis box="[420,503,667,693]" italics="true" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">papilio</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
’, meaning ‘butterfly’ and referring to the shape of the whorl profile.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
