<subSubSection lastPageId="22" lastPageNumber="89" pageId="21" pageNumber="88" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,372,1192,1218]" box="[227,372,1192,1218]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">
<heading bold="true" box="[227,372,1192,1218]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="21" pageNumber="88" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[227,372,1192,1218]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Description</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,1437,1238,1511]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">
<typeStatus box="[227,336,1238,1264]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Holotype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30470.1 is a phragocone segment of about a quarter whorl with almost 
<quantity box="[1275,1359,1239,1265]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="88" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
whorl height; it consists of four chambers (
<figureCitation box="[682,794,1274,1300]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[226,269,2001,2027]" captionTargetBox="[461,1200,1677,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-371@21.[459,1204,1670,1964]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 16. Vestinautilus papilio sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Holotype" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885236/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Fig. 16A</figureCitation>
). The whorl profile is depressed (ww/wh =1.62) and kidney-shaped with a rounded venter, subangular ventrolateral shoulder and a convex curved area encompassing the flanks and umbilical wall (
<figureCitation box="[748,856,1344,1370]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[227,270,896,922]" captionTargetBox="[228,1437,567,848]" captionTargetId="figure-351@22.[228,1437,567,848]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 17. Vestinautilus papilio sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30470.1. B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30470.1, at ww =15.5 mm, wh=9.5 mm.C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30470.2. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30470.2, at ww =10.3 mm, wh= 5.6 mm. Scale bar units= 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885240" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885240/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Fig. 17A</figureCitation>
). The whorl weakly encloses the preceding whorl. On the venter there are three longitudinal marginal grooves on each side; the ventrolateral shoulder is defined by two slightly raised edges. The flanks bear two coarse spiral lines near the ventrolateral shoulder. The suture line has a low amplitude course; it shows a very low external saddle and very shallow lateral lobe. Only the internal lobe is deeper and has a blunt V-shaped form (
<figureCitation box="[1221,1328,1485,1511]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[227,270,896,922]" captionTargetBox="[228,1437,567,848]" captionTargetId="figure-351@22.[228,1437,567,848]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 17. Vestinautilus papilio sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30470.1. B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30470.1, at ww =15.5 mm, wh=9.5 mm.C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30470.2. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30470.2, at ww =10.3 mm, wh= 5.6 mm. Scale bar units= 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885240" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885240/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Fig. 17B</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="21.[227,1437,1550,1612]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">
<typeStatus box="[227,330,1551,1577]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Paratype</typeStatus>
MB.C.30470.2 shows, at a whorl height of 
<quantity box="[849,917,1550,1577]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="21" pageNumber="88" unit="mm" value="6.0">6 mm</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[934,1041,1550,1576]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="21.[226,269,2001,2027]" captionTargetBox="[461,1200,1677,1958]" captionTargetId="figure-371@21.[459,1204,1670,1964]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="Fig. 16. Vestinautilus papilio sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Holotype" figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885236" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885236/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Fig. 16B</figureCitation>
), a largely similar morphology to the 
<typeStatus box="[270,377,1585,1611]" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">holotype</typeStatus>
. However, there is the big difference that it does not have a concave whorl zone (
<figureCitation box="[1317,1423,1585,1612]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="22.[227,270,896,922]" captionTargetBox="[228,1437,567,848]" captionTargetId="figure-351@22.[228,1437,567,848]" captionTargetPageId="22" captionText="Fig. 17. Vestinautilus papilio sp. nov. from Oued Temertasset (both Korn et al. 2002 Coll.). A. Whorl profile of holotype MB.C.30470.1. B. Suture line of holotype MB.C.30470.1, at ww =15.5 mm, wh=9.5 mm.C. Whorl profile of paratype MB.C.30470.2. D. Suture line of paratype MB.C.30470.2, at ww =10.3 mm, wh= 5.6 mm. Scale bar units= 1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6885240" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6885240/files/figure.png" pageId="21" pageNumber="88">Fig. 17C</figureCitation>
),
</paragraph>
